(2, 56, 'ABOUT US ARTICLE', 'about-us-article', '<div class="container_16">\r\n<div class="grid_16">\r\n<div class="wrapper about_top">\r\n<h2>About Black Rhino Resort</h2>\r\n<div class="col-md-6"><img class="img4" src="images/aboutus_1.jpg" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n<p class="about_heading">THE LODGE</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">The hidden treasure that is Black Rhino Game Lodge is one set amongst the trees of an old Tamboti forest at the foot of an ancient volcanic crater that boasts one of South Africa’s most exciting Big 5 eco-tourism destinations, the greater Pilanesberg National Park. The 58 000 hectares of wildlife wonderland and the magic of African bush, is the ideal location for a luxurious bushveld breakaway.</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">Located in the west side of the ‘Malaria Free’ Pilanesberg National Park, and only 33km from Sun City, The Black Rhino Game Lodge is built between a Tamboti forest, overlooking a busy waterhole, which is a hive of bird and animal activity, and a playground for the elephant. On many occasions, the stillness of the night is broken by the roaring of lions, and the franklins singing the morning wake up call.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wrapper  about_top">\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n<p class="about_heading">PILANSBERG NATIONAL PARK</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">Unlike any other national game park, the Pilanesberg hosts a combination of animal, bird, insect, reptilian and vegetation species, such as the Brown Hyena, Springbok, Red Eyed Bulbul and Camel Thorn tree. These species are normally found in dry areas, co-habitat with Impala, Black Eyed Bulbul and the Cape Chestnut trees are normally found in wetter areas. The Pilanesberg National Park is a perfect combination of the Kalahari and the wetter Lowveld. A major advantage of the Pilanesberg is that it is ‘Malaria Free’, which is not the case with other game parks further north. Sun City, best known for hosting the Million Dollar Golf Challenge and other spectacular events, lies on the border of the Pilanesberg, and is only a 33km drive from Black Rhino Game Reserve.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6"><img class="img4" src="images/aboutus_2.jpg" alt="" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wrapper">\r\n<p class="about_heading1">OUR EXCEPTIONAL STAFF</p>\r\n<div class="col-md-6"><div class="col-md-2 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Dale Hooper</p>\r\n<p class="pos">Lodge Manager</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">With his enthusiastic smile and emphasis on detail Dale will welcome you at Black Rhino GAME Lodge and ensure you have a memorable experience.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6"><div class="col-md-2 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Spencer Mkakza</p>\r\n<p class="pos">Duty and Entertainment Manager</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">Spencer, our Entertainment and Duty Manager, always goes above and beyond to ensure complete guest satisfaction, making sure that all your special needs are met.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wrapper">\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n<div class="col-md-6 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Rangers:</p>\r\n<p class="pos">Ruaan Schutte (Head Ranger), Matthew Soekoe, Johan Enslin, Phillip Jimu, Jenna Rossi.</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">Our ranger department consists of young enthusiastic and extremely talented individuals, who work together to ensure all those illusive animals are found.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n<div class="col-md-6 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Chefs</p>\r\n<p class="pos">Marelize Viljoen (Head Chef), Casper Eygelaar, Tish Moyo.</p>\r\n<p class="about_text">Our chefs are extremely diverse and work together to ensure that every meal is of top quality and appealing to guests from all over the world, and ensure that all dietary requirements is adhere to.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wrapper about_mid">\r\n<div class="col-md-4">\r\n<div class="col-md-4 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Bar attendants</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-4">\r\n<div class="col-md-4 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Waiters</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-4">\r\n<div class="col-md-4 image"><p>Photo Coming Soon</p></div>\r\n<p class="about_heading">Housekeepers</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wrapper">\r\n<div class="col-md-8 about_accom">\r\n<h2>Accomodation</h2>\r\n<div class="col-md-2"><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates"><img class="img4" src="images/aboutus_10.png" alt="" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2"><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates"><img class="img4" src="images/aboutus_11.png" alt="" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2"><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates"><img class="img4" src="images/aboutus_12.png" alt="" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-4 about_accom">\r\n<h2>facilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Bar and restaurant with deck</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Game drives and viewing</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Bird watching</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Swimming Pool</a></li>\r\n<li class="last"><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Laundry Service</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="area">\r\n<h2>Surrounding attractions</h2>\r\n<p><a href="/blackrhino/accommodation-rates">Golf (Sun City), Tour of the lost city , Elephant-back safaris , Balloon Trip over the Pilanesberg</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 1, 2, '2014-11-20 07:56:08', 939, '', '2014-12-19 07:45:30', 939, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-11-20 07:56:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"